  "text": "In summary, we conclude that the information encoded by aa composition of TM domains in polytopic proteins is valuable and sufficient in most cases to define the family relationship of a protein. In the few instances (Fig 5,6 ) that our algorithm performed poorly, it is suggested that the TM domains serve as localization anchors rather than being fundamental components of the family function. The effect on protein functions following replacement of an authentic TM domain by a lipid anchor had been monitored for certain protein families [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . In more general terms, considering proteins according to their broad definition, such as 'membranous', 'nuclear' etc. is useful for extracting additional 'nonalignment-based' information (such as TM aa composition, this study). The results could support classification and characterization efforts, especially for newly available but poorly annotated genomes.",
